J query is a library like bootstrap tht helps in coding stuffs really fast
instead of big javascript line we can go with
$("h2") - this is the document.querySelector("h2")

use google CDN for jquery
<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.6.0/jquery.min.js"></script>

always place jquery above js src
for changing
$("h1").css("color","red")

if both the cdn are in head give this function
$ (document).ready(function(){
$("h1").css("color","red")
})

instead of adding css directly to js
create a class in css then  add the class to  js
$("h1").addClass("classname")

for removing class
$("h1").removeClass("classname")
for adding many class just include it along followed witha space
.hasClass - for giving boolean values

for changing text
$("h1").text("classname")

for adding html 
$("h1").HTML("<em>hey</em>")

for getting the src
$("img").attr("src")
chnges the link
$("a").attr("href";https:yahoo)

for changing the color when clicked
$("h1").click(function(){
$("h1").css("color","red")
})

for getting the keystrokes
$("input").keypress(function(event){
console.log(event.key)
})

for changing the text of along with key stroke
$(document).keypress(function(event){
$("h1").text(event.key)
})

changing stuffs for mouseover
$("h1").on(function(){
$("h1").css("color","red")
})

for adding button b4 h1
$("h1").before("<btn>shaan</btn>")
.after , .prepend before the content , .append afterthe content

for removing stuffs
$("h1").remove()

animation 
$("button").on("click",function() {
$("h1").hide()
})
.toggle , .fadeOut , .fadeIn , .fadeToggle , .slideUp, .slideDown , .slideToggle , .animate({"opacity:0.5"}) use numerical values
all these can be added together using a dot stuff

